Dr. Vandana Gupta is currently working as Associate Professor at the Department of Microbiology, Ram Lal Anand College, University of Delhi. She did her B.Sc (Hons.) in
Microbiology from University of Delhi, followed by masters and Ph.D in Microbiology from Delhi University. She proceeded to Singapore for her Post doctoral work at Division of John
Hopkins at Singapore in Genetic immunotherapy lab and worked on Construction and validation of LAMP targeted and non LAMP targeted DNA vaccine against SARS virus. 

She also worked on analysis of B-cell and T-cell epitopes within spike and nucleocapsid proteins of SARS-CoV both experimentally as well as bioinformatically. Currently she is pursuing her
research in Bioinformatics with specialization in virtual screening of drugs against SARS-CoV-2, HCV, Chikungunya vurus, MRSA, ESBL-E. coli. 

Publications: She has a no. of research articles in peer reviewed International journals of
repute, book chapter and E learning resources and a patent to her credit. She is continuous
source of motivation to the students and has been invited to present her work Internationally.
